1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:06,031
That night, I didn't sleep. I wanted to
test it — this power I'd just taken. Was
it real?

2
00:00:06,631 --> 00:00:19,429
I pictured the scales on Madam Liu's back,
that knack for swallowing one's footsteps.
The next instant I rose from the couch
without a sound, crossing the broken
shards — not a whisper.

3
00:00:19,829 --> 00:00:26,104
Moonlight spilled in. I looked down — my
own shadow was three shades fainter than
my body. Stealth. It worked.

4
00:00:26,804 --> 00:00:34,841
But when I reached again for that brute
force she'd had before turning to smoke,
my chest wrenched as if two hands tore it
apart. It hurt.

5
00:00:35,241 --> 00:00:37,921
Same-origin rejection. One body holds but
a few arts at once; greed... brings
backlash.

6
00:00:38,521 --> 00:00:47,281
I cut the thought at once. I've survived
this long never by greed. However defiant
this bloodline, it has its rules — what
you can swallow, you may not master.

7
00:00:47,681 --> 00:00:52,481
So take only what matters, and grow
steadily. Eat one, grow one measure
stronger.

8
00:00:53,081 --> 00:01:01,002
In the dead of night I threw on Madam
Liu's empty robe and, with my new stealth,
slipped out past the ruined walls of the
cold palace.

9
00:01:01,402 --> 00:01:11,726
In the northwest corner stands an old
locust tree, three arms around. As I
neared, the dark-gold patterns beneath my
skin began to burn faintly — demonic aura.
Far thicker than by day.

10
00:01:12,326 --> 00:01:18,316
Under the tree crouched three "people."
Dressed as palace maids, but their faces
had long ceased to be human.

11
00:01:18,716 --> 00:01:29,621
One with a scale-covered face and
yellow-green vertical pupils; one with
twig-like fingers barbed at every joint;
the last, mouth split to the ears, baring
two rows of jagged teeth.

12
00:01:30,021 --> 00:01:32,429
Tsk... the Li family's cat — tender meat.

13
00:01:32,829 --> 00:01:39,162
Eat faster. Tonight we still collect rent
at the east court — Eunuch Liu said it's
Concubine Zhang's turn this month.

14
00:01:39,562 --> 00:01:46,459
Rent. I remembered what Xiaohe told me by
day — Concubine Zhang of the east court
hadn't been seen in three months.

15
00:01:46,859 --> 00:01:50,170
So it wasn't that she had vanished. She
had been taken as rent.

16
00:01:50,870 --> 00:02:00,640
I didn't rush to act. I was counting:
three demons, each with its own art. But
tonight I can swallow only one — so choose
the one most worth keeping on my own body.

17
00:02:01,040 --> 00:02:04,815
Gentlemen. This rent — on Concubine
Zhang's behalf, I'm calling it off.
